[3941.237894, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       are not sorted; brace expansion preserves left to right order.   For\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1835 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3941.279776, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       example, a\u001b[1m{\u001b[22md,c,b\u001b[1m}\u001b[22me expands into “ade ace abe”.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1836 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3964.379944, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1837 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3964.419293, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       A sequence expression takes the form \u001b[4mx\u001b[24m\u001b[1m..\u001b[4m\u001b[22my\u001b[24m\u001b[1m[..\u001b[4m\u001b[22mincr\u001b[24m\u001b[1m]\u001b[22m, where \u001b[4mx\u001b[24m and \u001b[4my\u001b[24m are\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1838 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3964.439319, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       either  integers or single letters, and \u001b[4mincr\u001b[24m, an optional increment,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1839 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3964.803704, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       is an integer.  When integers are supplied, the  expression  expands\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1840 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       to  each number between \u001b[4mx\u001b[24m and \u001b[4my\u001b[24m, inclusive.  If either \u001b[4mx\u001b[24m or \u001b[4my\u001b[24m begins\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1841 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3964.845534, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       with a zero, each generated term will contain  the  same  number  of\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1842 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3964.864689, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       digits,  zero-padding  where  necessary.  When letters are supplied,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1843 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       the expression expands to each character lexicographically between \u001b[4mx\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1844 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.144813, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       and \u001b[4my\u001b[24m, inclusive, using the C locale.  Note that both \u001b[4mx\u001b[24m and  \u001b[4my\u001b[24m  must\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1845 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.164999, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       be of the same type (integer or letter).  When the increment is sup‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1846 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[3965.165121, "o", "       plied,  it is used as the difference between each term.  The default\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1847 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.184875, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       increment is 1 or -1 as appropriate.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1848 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.185117, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1849 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.205774, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       Brace expansion is performed before any other  expansions,  and  any\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1850 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.489717, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       characters  special to other expansions are preserved in the result.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1851 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.489808, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       It is strictly textual.  \u001b[1mBash \u001b[22mdoes not apply any syntactic interpre‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1852 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.509591, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       tation to the context of the  expansion  or  the  text  between  the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1853 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       braces.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1854 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.529252, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1855 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       A correctly-formed brace expansion must contain unquoted opening and\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1856 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.548922, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       closing  braces, and at least one unquoted comma or a valid sequence\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1857 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.549291, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       expression.  Any incorrectly formed  brace  expansion  is  left  un‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1858 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.569169, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       changed.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1859 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1860 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.588928, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       A  “{”  or  Q  , may be quoted with a backslash to prevent its being\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1861 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.629131, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       considered part of a brace expression.  To avoid conflicts with  pa‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1862 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       rameter  expansion,  the  string “${” is not considered eligible for\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1863 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.64987, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       brace expansion, and inhibits brace expansion until the closing “}”.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1864 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.670411, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1865 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.691322, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       This construct is typically used as shorthand when the common prefix\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1866 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.731188, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       of the strings to be generated is longer than in the above example:\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1867 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.751563, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1868 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[3965.770922, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K              mkdir /usr/local/src/bash/{old,new,dist,bugs}\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1869 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
