[5858.673304, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[K\u001b[4mBASH\u001b[24m(1)                   General Commands Manual                   \u001b[4mBASH\u001b[24m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H\u001b[K       bash - GNU Bourne-Again SHell\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mbash \u001b[22m[options] [command_string | file]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mCOPYRIGHT\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K       Bash  is  Copyright  (C)  1989-2022 by the Free Software Foundation,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K       Inc.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mBash \u001b[22mis an \u001b[1msh\u001b[22m-compatible command language interpreter that  executes\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\u001b[K       commands read from the standard input or from a file.  \u001b[1mBash \u001b[22malso in‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[16;1H\u001b[K       corporates useful features from the \u001b[4mKorn\u001b[24m and \u001b[4mC\u001b[24m shells (\u001b[1mksh \u001b[22mand \u001b[1mcsh\u001b[22m).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[17;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[18;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mBash  \u001b[22mis intended to be a conformant implementation of the Shell and\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[19;1H\u001b[K       Utilities portion of the IEEE  POSIX  specification  (IE"]
[5858.673673, "o", "EE  Standard\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[20;1H\u001b[1;1H\u001b[K\u001b[4mBASH\u001b[24m(1)                   General Commands Manual                   \u001b[4mBASH\u001b[24m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[2;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[4;1H\u001b[K       bash - GNU Bourne-Again SHell\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[5;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[6;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mbash \u001b[22m[options] [command_string | file]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[8;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[9;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mCOPYRIGHT\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[10;1H\u001b[K       Bash  is  Copyright  (C)  1989-2022 by the Free Software Foundation,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[11;1H\u001b[K       Inc.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[12;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[13;1H\u001b[K\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[14;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mBash \u001b[22mis an \u001b[1msh\u001b[22m-compatible command language interpreter that  executes\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[15;1H\u001b[K       commands read from the standard input or from a file.  \u001b[1mBash \u001b[22malso in‐\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[16;1H\u001b[K       corporates useful features from the \u001b[4mKorn\u001b[24m and \u001b[4mC\u001b[24m shells (\u001b[1mksh \u001b[22mand \u001b[1mcsh\u001b[22m).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[17;1H\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[18;1H\u001b[K       \u001b[1mBash  \u001b[22mis intended to be a conformant implementation of the Shell and\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[19;1H\u001b[K       Utilities portion of the IEEE  PO"]
[5858.676648, "o", "SIX  specification  (IEEE  Standard\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[20;1H...skipping...\r\n              below  under  \u001b[1m\u001b[7mARITH\u001b[27m\u001b[1mMETIC EVALUATION\u001b[22m.  If the value of the ex‐\u001b[m\r\n              pression is non-zero, the return status is 0;  otherwise  the\u001b[m\r\n              return status is 1.  The \u001b[4mexpression\u001b[24m undergoes the same expan‐\u001b[m\r\n              sions  as  if  it were within double quotes, but double quote\u001b[m\r\n              characters in \u001b[4mexpression\u001b[24m are not treated  specially  and  are\u001b[m\r\n              removed.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m[[ \u001b[4m\u001b[22mexpression\u001b[24m \u001b[1m]]\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              Return  a status of 0 or 1 depending on the evaluation of the\u001b[m\r\n              conditional expression \u001b[4mexpression\u001b[24m.  Expressions are  composed\u001b[m\r\n              of  the  primaries  described below under \u001b[1mCONDITIONAL EXPRES‐\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mSIONS\u001b[22m.  The words between the \u001b[1m[[ \u001b[22mand \u001b[1m]] \u001b[22mdo not  undergo  word\u001b[m\r\n              splitting  and  pathname expansion.  The shell performs tilde\u001b[m\r\n              expansion, parameter and variable expansion,  arithmetic  ex‐\u001b[m\r\n              pansion,  command  substitution,  process  substitution,  and\u001b[m\r\n              quote removal on those words (the expansions that would occur\u001b[m\r\n              if the words were enclosed in  double  quotes).   Conditional\u001b[m\r\n              operators  such  as  \u001b[1m-f  \u001b[22mmust be unquoted to be recognized as\u001b[m\r\n              primaries.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 370/6908 5% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[5859.774202, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[5859.775549, "o", "...skipping...\r\n              to the rules described  below  under  \u001b[1m\u001b[7mARITH\u001b[27m\u001b[1mMETIC  EVALUATION\u001b[22m.\u001b[m\r\n              The  arithmetic expression \u001b[4mexpr2\u001b[24m is then evaluated repeatedly\u001b[m\r\n              until it evaluates to zero.  Each time \u001b[4mexpr2\u001b[24m evaluates  to  a\u001b[m\r\n              non-zero  value,  \u001b[4mlist\u001b[24m is executed and the arithmetic expres‐\u001b[m\r\n              sion \u001b[4mexpr3\u001b[24m is evaluated.  If any expression  is  omitted,  it\u001b[m\r\n              behaves  as  if  it  evaluates to 1.  The return value is the\u001b[m\r\n              exit status of the last command in \u001b[4mlist\u001b[24m that is executed,  or\u001b[m\r\n              false if any of the expressions is invalid.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mselect \u001b[4m\u001b[22mname\u001b[24m [ \u001b[1min \u001b[4m\u001b[22mword\u001b[24m ] ; \u001b[1mdo \u001b[4m\u001b[22mlist\u001b[24m ; \u001b[1mdone\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              The list of words following \u001b[1min \u001b[22mis expanded, generating a list\u001b[m\r\n              of  items,  and  the  set of expanded words is printed on the\u001b[m\r\n              standard error, each preced"]
[5859.775757, "o", "ed by a number.  If the \u001b[1min \u001b[4m\u001b[22mword\u001b[24m is\u001b[m\r\n              omitted, the positional parameters are printed  (see  \u001b[1mPARAME‐\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mTERS \u001b[22mbelow).  \u001b[1mselect \u001b[22mthen displays the \u001b[1mPS3 \u001b[22mprompt and reads a\u001b[m\r\n              line from the standard input.  If the line consists of a num‐\u001b[m\r\n              ber  corresponding  to  one  of the displayed words, then the\u001b[m\r\n              value of \u001b[4mname\u001b[24m is set to that word.  If the line is empty, the\u001b[m\r\n              words and prompt are displayed again.  If EOF  is  read,  the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 466/6908 7% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[5860.373921, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[5860.379838, "o", "...skipping...\r\n              \u001b[4mlength\u001b[24m and \u001b[4moffset\u001b[24m are arithmetic expressions (see  \u001b[1m\u001b[7mARITH\u001b[27m\u001b[4m\u001b[24m\u001b[1mMETIC\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[1mEVALUATION \u001b[22mbelow).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              If  \u001b[4moffset\u001b[24m evaluates to a number less than zero, the value is\u001b[m\r\n              used as an offset in characters from the end of the value  of\u001b[m\r\n              \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m.   If  \u001b[4mlength\u001b[24m evaluates to a number less than zero,\u001b[m\r\n              it is interpreted as an offset in characters from the end  of\u001b[m\r\n              the  value  of  \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m rather than a number of characters,\u001b[m\r\n              and the expansion is the characters between \u001b[4moffset\u001b[24m  and  that\u001b[m\r\n              result.   Note  that a negative offset must be separated from\u001b[m\r\n              the colon by at least one space to avoid being confused  with\u001b[m\r\n              the \u001b[1m:- \u001b[22mexpansion.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n              If \u001b[4mparameter\u001b[24m is \u001b[1m@ \u001b[22mor \u001b[1m*\u001b[22m, the result is \u001b[4mlength\u001b[24m positional para‐\u001b[m\r\n              meters beginning at \u001b[4moffset\u001b[24m.  A negative \u001b[4moffset\u001b[24m is taken rela‐\u001b[m\r\n              tive  to  one greater than the greatest positional parameter,\u001b[m\r\n              so an offset of -1 evaluates to the last  positional  parame‐\u001b[m\r\n              ter.   It is an expansion error if \u001b[4mlength\u001b[24m evaluates to a num‐\u001b[m\r\n              ber less than zero.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 1818/6908 27% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[5860.907244, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[5860.90894, "o", "...skipping...\r\n       der \u001b[1m\u001b[7mARITH\u001b[27m\u001b[1mMETIC EVALUATION\u001b[22m.  If \u001b[4mexpression\u001b[24m is invalid, \u001b[1mbash \u001b[22mprints  a\u001b[m\r\n       message indicating failure and no substitution occurs.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n   \u001b[1mProcess Substitution\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[4mProcess\u001b[24m  \u001b[4msubstitution\u001b[24m  allows  a process's input or output to be re‐\u001b[m\r\n       ferred to using a  filename.   It  takes  the  form  of  \u001b[1m<(\u001b[4m\u001b[22mlist\u001b[24m\u001b[1m)  \u001b[22mor\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m>(\u001b[4m\u001b[22mlist\u001b[24m\u001b[1m)\u001b[22m.   The  process \u001b[4mlist\u001b[24m is run asynchronously, and its input or\u001b[m\r\n       output appears as a filename.  This filename is passed as  an  argu‐\u001b[m\r\n       ment  to the current command as the result of the expansion.  If the\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m>(\u001b[4m\u001b[22mlist\u001b[24m\u001b[1m) \u001b[22mform is used, writing to the file  will  provide  input  for\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[4mlist\u001b[24m.   If  the \u001b[1m<(\u001b[4m\u001b[22mlist\u001b[24m\u001b[1m) \u001b[22mform is used, the file passed as an argument\u001b[m\r\n       should be read to obtain the output of \u001b[4mlist\u001b[24m.   Process  substitution\u001b[m\r\n       is  supported  on  systems  that  support named pipes (\u001b[4mFIFOs\u001b[24m) or the\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m/dev/fd \u001b[22mmethod of naming open files.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       When available, process  substitution  is  performed  simultaneously\u001b[m\r\n       with  parameter  and  variable  expansion, command substitution, and\u001b[m\r\n       arithmetic expansion.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 2080/6908 31% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[5861.627869, "o", "\r\u001b[K/\r\u001b[K"]
[5861.630987, "o", "...skipping...\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[7mARITH\u001b[27m\u001b[1mMETIC EVALUATION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       The  shell allows arithmetic expressions to be evaluated, under cer‐\u001b[m\r\n       tain circumstances (see the \u001b[1mlet \u001b[22mand \u001b[1mdeclare \u001b[22mbuiltin commands, the \u001b[1m((\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       compound command, and \u001b[1mArithmetic Expansion\u001b[22m).  Evaluation is done  in\u001b[m\r\n       fixed-width  integers with no check for overflow, though division by\u001b[m\r\n       0 is trapped and flagged as  an  error.   The  operators  and  their\u001b[m\r\n       precedence,  associativity, and values are the same as in the C lan‐\u001b[m\r\n       guage.  The following list of operators is grouped  into  levels  of\u001b[m\r\n       equal-precedence  operators.   The levels are listed in order of de‐\u001b[m\r\n       creasing precedence.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[4mid\u001b[24m\u001b[1m++ \u001b[4m\u001b[22mid\u001b[24m\u001b[1m--\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              variable post-increment and post-decrement\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m- +    \u001b[22munary minus and plus\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m++\u001b[4m\u001b[22mid\u001b[24m \u001b[1m--\u001b[4m\u001b[22mid\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n              variable pre-increment and pre-decrement\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m! ~    \u001b[22mlogical and bitwise negation\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m**     \u001b[22mexponentiation\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m* / %  \u001b[22mmultiplication, division, remainder\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 2660/6908 39% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[5864.680155, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       \u001b[1m+ -    \u001b[22maddition, subtraction\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 2661/6908 39% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[5864.845982, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       \u001b[1m<< >>  \u001b[22mleft and right bitwise shifts\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page bash(1) line 2662/6908 39% (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
